HEADWORD: Proglottis
<hw>Pro*glot"tis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Proglottides</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. fr. Gr.
<grk>proglwtti`s</grk> the tip of the tongue; <grk>pro`</grk> forward +
<grk>glw^tta</grk> the tongue.]</ety> <fld>(Zool)</fld> <def>One of the
free, or nearly free, segments of a tapeworm. It contains both male and
female reproductive organs, and is capable of a brief independent
existence.</def>⟦br⟧
